[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Problem:** The Python companion's third bullet of "things worth knowing upfront" correctly states: "production never carries [patient and case identifiers] past the Glue ETL boundary in the first place." This is the correct architectural posture (the consumption-history landing zone may carry case-level identifiers as the source-of-truth signal; the modeling-ready dataset should be de-identified at the Glue ETL boundary so that downstream SageMaker training, batch transform, forecast outputs, and DynamoDB serve layers operate on de-identified daily SKU counts). The main recipe should elevate this de-identification boundary as an architectural primitive rather than only an aside in the Python companion's preamble.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Fix:** Add a sentence to the BAA row or to the AWS Glue Why-These-Services paragraph naming the de-identification boundary at the Glue ETL layer as an architectural primitive. Suggested wording: "The Glue ETL layer is the de-identification boundary: case-level and patient-level identifiers may exist in the upstream consumption-history landing zone but are stripped before the modeling-ready dataset is written, so that downstream SageMaker, forecast, and DynamoDB-serve layers operate on daily SKU counts only."
