[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Location:** Prerequisites Encryption row covers SSE-KMS but does not name Object Lock or compliance-mode immutability for the model-artifact archive or the forecast-output archive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Problem:** Forecast records flow into purchase orders. The Why-This-Isn't-Production-Ready section's "Idempotency, audit trail, and rerun safety" gap correctly elevates the need for "an immutable audit log [that] captures which model version produced which reorder point." Object Lock in compliance mode on the model-artifact and forecast-output archive S3 buckets is the standard primitive for this immutability requirement.
