[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Voice consistency:** The Tuesday-afternoon community-hospital opening earns its position. The "Healthcare supply chains run on guesses dressed up as par levels" framing is the recipe's strongest single articulation of the operational-discipline-not-modeling-method posture and is consistent with CC's engineer-explaining-something-cool register. The "Hospital supply chain spend is typically the second-largest expense category after labor" pivot grounds the financial stakes appropriately. The "Nobody throws a party for a 15% reduction in supply chain working capital, but the CFO notices" closing of the Problem section is recipe-distinct and lands well. The Technology section's vocabulary lay-down (SKU, Demand, Lead time, Reorder point, Safety stock, Service level) is at the right grain for the mixed audience. The Honest Take's "materials managers don't sit around looking at forecasts. They live and die by par levels" trap is the recipe's strongest single piece of self-deprecating-expertise and earns its position. The "the value isn't in the forecast itself, it's in the reorder point updates" framing is the recipe's clearest articulation of the integration-layer-as-load-bearing posture.
